      <section eId="sec_13_7_13">
        <num>13-7-13</num>
        <content>
          <p>Recoupment may be pleaded in all actions ex contractu where the plaintiff is liable to the defendant under the same contract.</p>
          <p>If the damages of the defendant exceed those of the plaintiff, the defendant shall be awarded the amount of such excess from the plaintiff.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2853; Code 1868, § 2861; Code 1873, § 2912; Ga. L. 1878-79, p. 147, § 1; Code 1882, § 2912; Civil Code 1895, § 3759; Civil Code 1910, § 4353; Code 1933, § 20-1314.)</p>
        </content>
      </section>
